{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/CodeEditSourceEditor","doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/TextViewController"],"title":"Text View","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"GutterView","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the gutter needs more space (when the number of digits in the numbers increases eg. adding a line after line 99),","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it will notify it’s delegate via the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterViewDelegate\/gutterViewWidthDidUpdate(newWidth:)"},{"text":" method. In","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CodeEditSourceEditor"},{"text":", this notifies the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/TextViewController","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", which in turn updates the textview’s edge insets"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to adjust for the new leading inset.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This view also listens for selection updates, and draws a selected background on selected lines to keep the illusion"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that the gutter’s line numbers are inline with the line itself.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The gutter view has insets of it’s own that are relative to the widest line index. By default, these insets are 20px","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lead